Description: Three fragments of shoulder of Fikellura pottery amphora: two joined, with base of triple-handle, one separate but joining; both white slipped. Neck, meander and square. Shoulder, tongues: dividing band of strokes alternately up and down: open cable. Belly, chain of buds (with bar above bud).
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", east annex (G), chamber 18
Curator's comments: Three sherds re-registered 1924,1201.1046, 1924,1201.1049 and 1924,1201.1097 Findspot number '18' scratched on reverse of 1924,1201.1046.
Bibliographic references: CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (Pl. GB 576, 9)
Weber 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus anderen ägyptischen Fundorten (TD 224)
